OL,6,FHis injuries included a fractured
OL,7,Fskull, a bleed on the brain, a broken
OL,8,Fspine, and multiple internal injuries.
OL,10,FMembers of the public helped the
OL,11,Femergency services with the victim and
OL,12,Fwith Roberts who was described as
OL,13,Fbeing intoxicated by the roadside.
OL,15,FIn custody, Roberts tested positive
OL,16,Ffor 121 micrograms (uhg) of alcohol
OL,17,Fper 100 millilitres (ml) of breath.
OL,18,FThe legal limit is 35uhg of alcohol
OL,19,Fper 100ml of breath.
